This paper deals with graph theory and specifically focuses on the queue-number of graphs with bounded tree-width. The paper presents upper and lower bounds on the queue-number of graphs, which is a combinatorial problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper involves the study of graph embeddings and layouts, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also uses techniques from graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.GT (Graph Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
